What is the lowest level you believe you ever saw 🌌 ? Light pollution, the excessive or misdirected artificial light produced by human activities, severely impacts the visibility of the celestial night sky. It obscures the beauty of heavenly bodies, diminishing our ability to observe stars, planets, and other celestial phenomena, thereby severing a vital connection to our cosmic environment. Astronomers and stargazers face significant challenges as the glaring, scattered light interferes with the clarity of astronomical observations. Light pollution also disrupts ecosystems, affecting nocturnal animals by altering their natural behaviors and circadian rhythms. Efforts like shielding outdoor lighting can mitigate these effects, preserving the pristine darkness of the night sky and protecting the ecological balance of nocturnal habitats. The diminishment of light pollution is crucial for scientific discovery and maintaining our celestial heritage. Like our content? Follow @spacextian for more Follow @spacextian for more! 🍰 Why Cut Cake on Birthdays? The Mythical Tale! 🌕 Ever wondered why we celebrate with cake instead of pizza or samosas? 🍕 Here’s a surprising answer: It dates back to ancient Greece! 🇬🇷 In Greek mythology, there’s Artemis, the moon goddess. On her birthday, people offered a round cake, symbolizing the moon’s shape. 🌝 Those candles? They were there to make the cake shine like the moon! 🕯️ This symbolism spread from Greece to Europe and eventually the world. Yet, it remains more of a Western tradition. 🌍 Ask your Indian grandparents, and you’ll discover that birthdays here are still celebrated with food, but not cake. Instead, it’s delicious Indian desserts like kheer or Payasam! 🍚🎉 #BirthdayTraditions #CakeHistory #birthdaycake

A gated entrance introduces the estate which spans over 3.8 acres in the heart of the revered Langley Farms neighborhood, distinguishing it as one of the largest estates in this storied enclave. A gracious driveway leads through meticulous gardens and specimen trees to reveal the 22,000 square foot, limestone and brick mansion discretely positioned on the top of the hill. Massive wrought-iron doors introduce the interiors which are both grand in proportions and finishes. An impressive plaster dome soars above the foyer and hints at the intricate plaster molding and custom finishes found throughout the home. Italian marble blends seamlessly with contemporary white oak hardwoods and forged iron railings. Throughout the estate, dozens of custom crystal chandeliers illuminate throughout the expansive and open floor plan. A richly paneled library is located just off the entry hall to welcome visitors or to provide a perfect retreat for work. Just beyond, the grand ballroom appointed with floor-to-ceiling mirrors was inspired by the opulence of the Palace of Versailles. Upstairs, the primary suite spans a total of 3,300 square feet and boasts panoramic views of the pool and the gardens beyond. Not to be overshadowed, the primary closet encompasses 1,100 square feet and spans two levels with the finest Italian cabinetry and custom lighting throughout. The nine additional bedroom suites are also gracious and include ensuite baths featuring stunning mosaic work and beautiful views of the gardens. Hey guys, Rick here to explain the meme. The joke here starts out with someone searching the words “I hate it when.” Below this there’s two suggestions on what google thinks you’re going to say to finish your search. The first suggestion is “I hate it when my dog and cat steal my fridge” and the second one is “I hate it when I go outside and someone randomly throws a fridge at me.” Now these are some of the most random search suggestions ever because there’s no way those suggestions are literal things that happen to people. Below this there are two images to represent what the search results say. The first one shows a dog and a cat stealing your fridge and then the following image shows them then throwing the fridge at you when you walk inside. These images are here to show how absolutely absurd it is for these to be the common search results since it’s impossible for this kind of thing to happen. Also the person reading this, I hope you have a great day & if you’re seeing me on your explore page & you’ve read this far you might as well follow @rick.explains as I explain memes like this all the time! - #makemelaugh #hilariousmeme #laughterisgoodforthesoul #relatables #funniest #cantstoplaughing #memesforyou #funnymemes😂 #lmaooo #savagememesdaily #dailydankmemes #memegod #memepagepurge #sorelatable #funnypost #laughsohard #memesforlife #memepages #memereview #textposts #memed #memeinstagram #dankmemesmeltsteelbeams #dankestmemes

Without any gear, you would survive for less than 2 minutes. ✩Venus It is a real hell. The temperature on its surface is approximately 400 C. Its surface pressure is also about 90 times greater than that of Earth. A spacesuit designed for Venus would need to be constructed of titanium.
